6. Final settlement
:SKRSLUT.
:SWISS8.
.sp 3mm
In the event of default in connection with netting, &BANKNAVN. may claim
final settlement. The final settlement may be carried out in any present
or future obligation between the customer and &BANKNAVN. which entitles to
cash settlement, e.g. deposits and loans, guarantee obligations, rights
obtained by transfer and claim for delivery of securities, including
return of securities transferred to &BANKNAVN. as pledge/mortgage or
ownership. Claims covered by framework agreements regarding
currency, interest, index and security transactions are finally settled
according to such agreements.
.br
.kp off
.kp on
On final settlement, the current value of the obligations between
&BANKNAVN. and the customer is calculated in Danish kroner or in another
currency, if agreed. Claims protected by agreement of financial security
or other security are reduced by the revenue of realised security.
.br
.kp off
.kp on
The obligations settled are cleared as one net outstanding account. If
final settlements take place at the same time, &BANKNAVN. may choose to
let the balances in question be included in one overall, total final
settlement. &BANKNAVN. will notify the customer of the final
settlement. &BANKNAVN. may later adjust the balance of the final settlement
by the revenue from subsequent realisation of obligations, finally
settled claims according to obligations, which can only be settled
at a later point in time, e.g. guarantee obligations, or claims which are
due at a later point in time.
.br
Transfer of a claim against &BANKNAVN. to third party must respect the
right of &BANKNAVN. to carry out final settlement.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.*.kp on
